emojo.com/movies/?id=dcfilm1117.htm|archive-date=November 19, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2018\n| ''[[Teen Titans Go! To the Movies]]''\n| [[Aaron Horvath]] & Peter Rida Michail\n|'''Screenplay by''' Aaron Horvath & [[Michael Jelenic]]\n|{{based on|''[[Teen Titans]]''|[[Bob Haney]] and [[Bruno Premiani]]}}<br />{{Based on|''[[Teen Titans Go! (TV series)|Teen Titans Go!]]''|Aaron Horvath and Michael Jelenic}}\n| Warner Bros. / [[Warner Bros. Animation]]<ref name=\"insight-Feb2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|title=Film releases|work=[[Variety Insight]]|accessdate=May 9, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180205105405/http://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|archive-date=February 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| $10&nbsp;million<ref name=\"BOMTeenTitans2018\">{{cite web |title=Teen Titans Go! To The Movies |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=wbanimation62018.htm |website=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=September 6, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180819123312/https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=wbanimation62018.htm |archive-date=August 19, 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref>\n| $51.9&nbsp;million<ref name=\"BOMTeenTitans2018\" />\n|-\n| ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]''\n| [[James Wan]]\n| '''Story by''' James Wan and [[Geoff Johns]] <br />'''Screenplay by''' [[Will Beall]]\n| ''[[Aquaman]]'' by [[Mort Weisinger]] and [[Paul Norris]]\n| [[Warner Bros.]] / DC Entertainment / [[Cruel & Unusual Films]]<ref name=\"insight-Sept2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180923132936/https://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|title=Film releases|work=[[Variety Insight]]|archivedate=September 23, 2018|accessdate=September 23, 2018}}</ref>\n| $160&nbsp;million<ref>{{cite web|authorlink1=14 December 2016|title=Aquaman Budget And Filming Location Reveale